   <TextArea layoutX="8.0" layoutY="61.0" prefHeight="331.0" prefWidth="584.0"
             text="This game is the product of a project that is mandatory on the first semester of Software Engeneering.&#10;The goal of the project is to further develop on a game called &quot;World of Zuul&quot;, and have the game inform the player about FN's 17 global goals. &#10;&#10;On our take of the project we went with the global goals: &#10;- Nr 9 - Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure&#10;- Nr 13 - Climate Action&#10;- Nr 15 - Life On Land&#10;&#10;We wanted to inform the player about the phosphorus problems, we have in the current state of the world. &#10;In our opinion there isn't nearly enough information about the problems. &#10;It is often overlooked by the other pollution problems we currently have.&#10;Also in our game, we want to inform the player about the solutions that are currently beeing developed in different parts of the world.&#10;The purification plant, biofarm and the other different project that are available to support on the university is an implication of this.&#10;&#10;One of the most prominent problems with phoshorus, is the fact that we are rapidly depleating the phosphorus mines of the important minerals.&#10;The mineral in and of itself is one of the most essential minerals in our life, because it amplifies the outcome from agriculture so significantly.&#10;Not only does phosphorus amplify agriculture, it is also an essential mineral in life.&#10;No-one can live without phosphorus, not humans, not animals and not even plants.&#10;The reason phosphorus is so essential, is because it is used by our bodies in of cell membranes, for energy transfering in all living cells,&#10;and is even citical for our teeth and bones.&#10;Therefore you can even say, without phosphorus there would be no life on earth.&#10;But on the bright side, the research into reusing the phosphorus from our sewers is in development. &#10;Other ways of handling the problems, that are in the works as of this moment is:&#10;improving our use of phosphorus in agriculture with the use of micro-organisms, along with smart cleaning of lakes.&#10;&#10;Even though the game only shows a single city, a small lake and a single farm, this world is meant to repressent the entire world we live in.&#10;The city is all of the cities in the world, the farm is the entire agriculture of the world, &#10;and the small lake is all the lakes, rivers and water springs that are scattered throughout the world.&#10;&#10;&#10;So if there is a single important thing to take away from playing this game it should be:&#10;Even if something seems sustanable, it might not be, and even if it's not everywhere in the news, &#10;there are still other acts out there that is damaging not only our fresh water, not only our land, but is distroying entire civilizations.&#10;&#10;This game was developed by:&#10;Frederik Karlsmose Svarer&#10;Lars Kristiansen &#10;Oliver Bartelings &#10;Peter Tran &#10;Nikandras Kinderis "
